 Godwin Emefiele, governor of Nigeria’s central bank, .Photographer: Chris J. Ratcliffe/Bloomberg via Getty Images  Any remaining hopes of an interest rate cut by the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) in the near term have been quashed by signs of rising inflationary pressures, which touched a 17-month high of 11.61 per cent, over unending food prices.
 
